<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1087,1112]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is taken from a diagnostic character of this species (the translucent yellow abdomen); it is derived from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis box="[693,760,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">flavus</emphasis>
(yellow).
</paragraph>
