<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1196,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[929,1010,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Billaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[929,1010,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Billaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having fine black hairs on upper parafacial, 
<number box="[278,292,1231,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="5.0">5</number>
distinct black longitudinal vittae on presutural scutum, reddish yellow femora and tibiae, abdomen translucent yellow, and gray white pruinosity only on anterior margin of tergites 
<number box="[1054,1068,1268,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[1122,1139,1268,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="4.0">4</number>
.
</paragraph>
